aa(lp34
VLet me tell you a little bit about this chemistry of oil.
p35
aVOil is a stew of hydrocarbon molecules.
p36
aVIt starts of with the very small ones,
p37
aVwhich are one carbon, four hydrogen \u2014
p38
aVthat's methane \u2014 it just floats off.
p39
aVThen there's all sorts of intermediate ones with middle amounts of carbon.
p40
aVYou've probably heard of benzene rings; they're very carcinogenic.
p41
aVAnd it goes all the way over
p42
aVto these big, thick, galumphy ones that have hundreds of carbons,
p43
aVand they have thousands of hydrogens,
p44
aVand they have vanadium and heavy metals and sulfur
p45
aVand all kinds of craziness hanging off the sides of them.
p46
aVThose are called the asphaltenes; they're an ingredient in asphalt.
p47
aVThey're very important in oil spills.
p48
aa(lp49
VLet me tell you a little bit about
p50
aVthe chemistry of oil in water.
p51
aVIt is this chemistry that makes oil so disastrous.
p52
aVOil doesn't sink, it floats.
p53
aVIf it sank, it would be a whole different story as far as an oil spill.
p54
aVAnd the other thing it does is it spreads out the moment it hits the water.
p55
aVIt spreads out to be really thin,
p56
aVso you have a hard time corralling it.
p57
aVThe next thing that happens
p58
aVis the light ends evaporate,
p59
aVand some of the toxic things float into the water column
p60
aVand kill fish eggs
p61
aVand smaller fish and things like that, and shrimp.
p62
aVAnd then the asphaltenes \u2014 and this is the crucial thing \u2014
p63
aVthe asphaltenes get whipped by the waves
p64
aVinto a frothy emulsion, something like mayonnaise.
p65
aVIt triples the amount
p66
aVof oily, messy goo that you have in the water,
p67
aVand it makes it very hard to handle.
p68
aVIt also makes it very viscous.
p69
aVWhen the Prestige sank off the coast of Spain,
p70
aVthere were big, floating cushions the size of sofa cushions
p71
aVof emulsified oil,
p72
aVwith the consistency, or the viscosity, of chewing gum.
p73
aVIt's incredibly hard to clean up.
p74
aVAnd every single oil is different when it hits water.
p75
