aa(lp210
VSo the thing about water oil spills
p211
aVis that they are very politically galvanizing.
p212
aVI mean, these pictures \u2014 this is from the Santa Barbara spill.
p213
aVYou have these pictures of birds.
p214
aVThey really influence people.
p215
aVWhen the Santa Barbara spill happened in 1969,
p216
aVit formed the environmental movement in its modern form.
p217
aVIt started Earth Day.
p218
aVIt also put in place the National Environmental Policy Act,
p219
aVthe Clean Air Act, the Clean Water Act.
p220
aVEverything that we are really stemmed from this period.
p221
aVI think it's important to kind of look at these pictures of the birds
p222
aVand understand what happens to us.
p223
aVHere we are normally;
p224
aVwe're standing at the gas pump, and we're feeling kind of helpless.
p225
aVWe look at these pictures
p226
aVand we understand, for the first time, our role in this supply chain.
p227
aVWe connect the dots in the supply chain.
p228
aVAnd we have this kind of \u2014
p229
aVas voters, we have kind of a "eureka!" moment.
p230
aVThis is why these moments of these oil spills
p231
aVare so important.
p232
aVBut it's also really important that we don't get distracted
p233
aVby the theater or the morals of it.
p234
aVWe actually need to go in
p235
aVand work on the roots of the problem.
