aa(lp237
VOne of the things that happened with the two previous oil spills
p238
aVwas that we really worked on some of the symptoms.
p239
aVWe were very reactive, as opposed to being proactive
p240
aVabout what happened.
p241
aVAnd so what we did was, actually,
p242
aVwe made moratoriums on the east and west coasts on drilling.
p243
aVWe stopped drilling in ANWR,
p244
aVbut we didn't actually reduce the amount of oil that we consumed.
p245
aVIn fact, it's continued to increase.
p246
aVThe only thing that really reduces the amount of oil that we consume
p247
aVis much higher prices.
p248
aVAs you can see, our own production has fallen off
p249
aVas our reservoirs have gotten old and expensive to drill out.
p250
aVWe only have two percent of the world's oil reserves;
p251
aV65 percent of them are in the Persian Gulf.
