aVAlso, every time you buy gasoline in the United States,
p317
aVhalf of it is actually being refined along the coast,
p318
aVbecause the Gulf actually has
p319
aVabout 50 percent of our refining capacity
p320
aVand a lot of our marine terminals as well.
