aa(lp324
VAnd finally, American families also pay a price for oil.
p325
aVNow on the one hand, the price at the pump is not really very high
p326
aVwhen you consider the actual cost of the oil,
p327
aVbut on the other hand,
p328
aVthe fact that people have no other transit options
p329
aVmeans that they pay a large amount of their income
p330
aVinto just getting back and forth to work,
p331
aVgenerally in a fairly crummy car.
p332
aVIf you look at people who make $50,000 a year, they have two kids,
p333
aVthey might have three jobs or more,
p334
aVand then they have to really commute.
