aa(lp344
VSo, what I'm going to talk to you about now is:
p345
aVwhat do we have to do this time?
p346
aVWhat are the laws? What do we have to do to keep ourselves focused?
p347
aVOne thing is \u2014 we need to stay away from the theater.
p348
aVWe need to stay away from the moratoriums.
p349
aVWe need to focus really back again
p350
aVon the molecules.
p351
aVThe moratoriums are fine, but we do need to focus
p352
aVon the molecules on the oil.
p353
aVOne of the things that we also need to do,
p354
aVis we need to try to not kind of fool ourselves
p355
aVinto thinking that you can have a green world,
p356
aVbefore you reduce the amount of oil that we use.
p357
aVWe need to focus on reducing the oil.
p358
aa(lp359
VWhat you see in this top drawing is a schematic
p360
aVof how petroleum gets used in the U.S. economy.
p361
aVIt comes in on the side \u2014 the useful stuff is the dark gray,
p362
aVand the un-useful stuff,
p363
aVwhich is called the rejected energy \u2014 the waste,
p364
aVgoes up to the top.
p365
aVNow you can see that the waste far outweighs
p366
aVthe actually useful amount.
